<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Princely" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Princely,</orth> 1) pertaining to, or coming from, a prince: <cit><quote>woundest his p. name,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 599" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 599</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy p. office,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 599" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 599</bibl></cit> <cit><quote>hid my p. trunk,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.86" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 86</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. feet before,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.92" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 92</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your p. knee,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 190</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. favour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 5.6.42" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 6, 42</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 3.2.17" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A III, 2, 17</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.66" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 1.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 I, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.143" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.143" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 143</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 1, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.51" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.118" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 118</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.3.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 3, 93</bibl>.<lb />2) of the rank of princes (and hence == high, august, royal): <cit><quote>her p. guest,</quote> <bibl n="shak. luc 90" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 90</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>these p. suitors,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 2, 38</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>thy p. son,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.484" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 484</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 58</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.141" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.1.173" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 173</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 3.3.38" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.1.18" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 18</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.3.17" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 17</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.152" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 152</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.72" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.1.166" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 1, 166</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.1" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.6.51" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 6, 51</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.7.27" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 7, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.280" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 280</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.228" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 228</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.228" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 4, 228</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 29</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 29</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 29</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 29</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.1.34" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.3.20" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.88" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 5, 88</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.405" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 405</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.174" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 174</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.429" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 429</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 93</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 171</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 4.2.171" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 171</bibl> <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.360" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 360</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.360" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 360</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 1.3.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 3, 33</bibl>.
<lb />3) becoming a prince: <cit><quote>a p. testimony!</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.317" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 317</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>his p. exercises,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.2.37" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 2, 37</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. liberty,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.140" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 140</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>p. care,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 49</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.266" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 266</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.100" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 100</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 3.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 16</bibl>.
<lb />4) high-minded, noble: <cit><quote>his p. heart,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 1.267" default="NO" valid="yes">John I, 267</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that young and p. gentleman,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.1.175" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 1, 175</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>trimmed up your praises with a p. tongue,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 5.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A V, 2, 57</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>as full of valour as of kindness, p. in both,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 3, 16</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he was most p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 2, 57</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.1.91" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 1, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.5.279" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 5, 279</bibl>, <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 22</bibl>.
<lb />5) magnificent, majestic: <cit><quote>her p. gait,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.261" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. II, 261</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>too precious p. for a grave,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 4.3.40" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 3, 40</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>beauty's p. majesty is such,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 70</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>most p. gifts,</quote> <bibl n="shak. cor 1.9.80" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 9, 80</bibl></cit>.
<lb />Adverbially: <cit><quote>my appetite was not p. got,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.2.12" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 2, 12</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>